Kanu secretary general Nick Salat is working closely with his advocates to patent the &ldquo;Niko ndaani ndaani ndaaani&rdquo; catchphrase and derive benefits from it. The quote, which has now become popular, was first uttered by Salat while addressing a crowd during the launch of Nasa on February 22.Reactions include: Steve Oyugi: It will be obsolete soon like 'thitima' 'kerroro' etc. Peter Gichuhi: Nganga: Sema kukosa kazi.Thomas Mweu: Nzissi: Ata Ndaaaani, Ndaaaani inawesa kuwa chama.Oscar El Kara&ntilde;ja: He should legalize it, trademark it!